FBIS4-746 "drafr073_d_94018" FBIS-AFR-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Mozambique UN Italian Forces To Withdraw for Financial Reasons UN Italian Forces To Withdraw for Financial Reasons MB1504093394 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network in English 1800 GMT 14 Apr 94 MB1504093394 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network English BFN [Text] The battalion of 1,000 Italian troops stationed in central Mozambique as part of the United Nations peacekeeping operation will start withdrawing from the country this week. The charge d'affaires of the Italian Embassy in Maputo, (Cristiano Galli), said today that 150 soldiers were to leave at the weekend and that the entire battalion would [words indistinct] April or early May. (Galli) said that the Italian Government could no longer afford [words indistinct] which cost (?it) about $10 million a month in Mozambique.
